{
  "text": "Even in the presence of the parity-violating terms, spherically symmetric solutions remain the same as in general relativity [CITATION_1] if \u03c6 is minimally coupled to matter and gravity (except for the gravitational parity-violating part). In this case, we may set G N = G. Then, the binary-pulsar constraint is translated to |k\u03b1| 5 \u00d7 10 \u22123 , or \u039b \u22121 |\u03b1| 10 6 km ,",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2243511"
